bench

Class TestContext.TestParam

  • java.lang.Object
    • bench.TestContext.TestParam
  • Enclosing class:
    TestContext

    public static final class TestContext.TestParam
extends java.lang.Object
    Inner class to manage format and definitions for all parameters. All parameter names are coerced to lower case before being stored, to minimize the risk of mixed case spelling errors. Two static collections are managed within this class, one to support name-based lookup and the other to support output in printout sequence (including category names).

        public TestContext.TestParam(java.lang.String paramNameIn,
                     int type)
        Special constructor for miscellaneous String param types, including USER_PARAM and CATEGORY_PARAM.
        Parameters:
        paramNameIn - For USER_PARAM type, the Property key, for CATEGORY_PARAM the display text.
        type - Must be USER_PARAM or CATEGORY_PARAM

      • TestContext.TestParam

        public TestContext.TestParam(java.lang.String paramNameIn,
                     java.lang.String helpTxtIn,
                     bench.TestContext.ComputedValue valueIn)
        Constructor for computed parameters. These params are computed based on a Java object that implements the ComputedValue interface. There should never be a case where a default value is required.
        Parameters:
        paramNameIn - Parameter name; by convention all computed value parameters use prefix '$'.
        helpTxtIn - Help text description for interactive and documentation purposes.
        valueIn - An instance of ComputedValue used to dynamically compute a string result.
